      "title": "Equation of chord with eccentric angle",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Equation of the chord of the ellipse whose eccentric angles are $\\theta $ and $\\phi $ :&nbsp;</strong></h3><p>Let the ellipse be $\\frac{{{x}^{2}}}{{{a}^{2}}}+\\frac{{{y}^{2}}}{{{b}^{2}}}=1$ ...(i)</p><p>Let $\\text{P}\\,\\,\\left( \\text{a cos}\\,\\theta ,\\text{b}\\,\\text{sin}\\,\\theta \\right)$ and $\\text{Q}\\,\\,\\left( \\text{a}\\,\\text{cos}\\,\\phi ,\\text{b}\\,\\text{sin}\\,\\phi \\right)$ be two points on ellipse (1).</p><p>Equation of chord $\\text{PQ}$ is</p><p>$\\text{y}-\\text{b}\\sin \\theta =\\frac{\\text{b}(\\sin \\theta -\\sin \\phi )}{\\text{a}(\\cos \\theta -\\cos \\phi )}(\\text{x}-\\text{a}\\cos \\theta )$.</p><p>$=\\frac{\\text{b}}{\\text{a}}\\frac{2\\cos \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}\\sin \\frac{\\theta -\\phi }{2}}{2\\sin \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}\\sin \\frac{\\phi -\\theta }{2}}(\\text{x}-\\text{a}\\cos \\theta )$</p><p>or $\\left( \\frac{\\text{y}-\\text{b}\\sin \\theta }{\\text{b}} \\right)\\sin \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}=-\\left( \\frac{\\text{x}-\\text{a}\\cos \\theta }{\\text{a}} \\right)\\cos \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}$</p><p>or $\\frac{\\text{y}}{\\text{b}}\\sin \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}-\\sin \\theta \\sin \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}=-\\frac{\\text{x}}{\\text{a}}\\cos \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}+\\cos \\theta \\cos \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}$</p><p>or $\\frac{\\text{x}}{\\text{a}}\\cos \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}+\\frac{\\text{y}}{\\text{b}}\\sin \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}=\\cos \\left( \\theta -\\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2} \\right)$</p><p>or $\\frac{x}{a}cos\\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}+\\frac{y}{b}\\sin \\frac{\\theta +\\phi }{2}=\\cos \\frac{\\theta -\\phi }{2}$</p><p><strong>Note : </strong>When $\\phi \\to \\theta $, chord $\\text{PQ}$ becomes tangent at $\\text{P}$</p><p><strong>∴ </strong>Equation of tangent at $\\text{P}\\,(\\text{a}\\cos \\theta ,\\text{b}\\sin \\theta )\\,\\,is\\,\\,\\frac{\\text{x}}{\\text{a}}\\cos \\,\\,\\theta \\,\\,+\\,\\,\\frac{\\text{y}}{\\text{b}}\\,\\,\\sin \\,\\,\\theta =1$</p><p><strong>Equation of the chord of the ellipse $\\frac{{{x}^{2}}}{{{a}^{2}}}+\\frac{{{y}^{2}}}{{{b}^{2}}}=1$ whose middle point is $\\left( {{x}_{1}},{{y}_{1}} \\right)$.&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" width=\"362\" height=\"250\">&nbsp;</p><p>Given ellipse is $\\frac{{{x}^{2}}}{{{a}^{2}}}+\\frac{{{y}^{2}}}{{{b}^{2}}}=1$ ...(i)</p><p>Let $\\text{P}\\left( {{\\text{x}}_{1}},{{\\text{y}}_{1}} \\right)$ be the middle point of a chord</p><p>$\\text{AB}$ of the ellipse (1), then the required equation is</p><p>or \\(\\frac{\\mathrm{xx}_1}{\\mathrm{a}^2}+\\frac{\\mathrm{yy}_1}{\\mathrm{~b}^2}-1=\\frac{\\mathrm{x}_1^2}{\\mathrm{a}^2}+\\frac{\\mathrm{y}_1^2}{\\mathrm{~b}^2}-1\\)</p><p>or $\\text{T}={{\\text{S}}_{1}}$</p><p>where $\\text{T}$ and ${{\\text{S}}_{1}}$ have usual meanings.</p>",
      "position": 0,
