      "title": "equation of chord when its midpoint is given",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Equation of the chord of the parabola which is bisected at a given point&nbsp;</strong></h3><p>The equation of the chord of the parabola ${{y}^{2}}=4ax$ which is bisected at $\\left( {{x}_{1}},{{y}_{1}} \\right)$ is</p><p>$\\text{y}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-2\\text{a}\\left( \\text{x}+{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right)=\\text{y}_{1}^{2}-4\\text{a}{{\\text{x}}_{1}}\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ or }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ T}=\\text{{S}'}$</p><p>where $\\text{{S}'}=\\text{y}_{1}^{2}-4\\text{a}{{\\text{x}}_{1}}$ and $\\text{T}=\\text{y}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-2\\text{a}\\left( \\text{x}+{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right)$.</p><p><strong>Proof : </strong>The equation of a line passing through $\\left( {{\\text{x}}_{1}},{{\\text{y}}_{1}} \\right)$ is $\\text{y}-{{\\text{y}}_{1}}=\\text{m}\\left( \\text{x}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right)$</p><p>where $m$ is a variable.</p><p>The abscissa of the points of intersection of ${{y}^{2}}=4\\text{ax}$ and (ii) are the roots of the equation</p><p>${{\\left( {{\\text{y}}_{1}}-\\text{m}{{\\text{x}}_{1}}+\\text{mx} \\right)}^{2}}=4\\text{ax}$</p><p>or ${{\\text{m}}^{2}}{{\\text{x}}^{2}}+2\\left\\{ -2\\text{a}+\\text{m}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-{{\\text{m}}^{2}}{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right\\}\\text{x}+{{\\left( {{\\text{y}}_{1}}-\\text{m}{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right)}^{2}}=0$</p><p>Let ${{\\text{p}}_{1}}$ and ${{\\text{p}}_{2}}$ be the roots of this equation. Then,</p><p>${{\\text{p}}_{1}}+{{\\text{q}}_{2}}=\\frac{-2\\left\\{ -2\\text{a}+\\text{m}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-{{\\text{m}}^{2}}{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right\\}}{{{\\text{m}}^{2}}}$</p><p>Since $\\left( {{x}_{1}},{{y}_{1}} \\right)$ is the mid-point of the chord joining the points of intersection</p><p>of (i) and the parabola.</p><p>$\\therefore \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }{{\\text{x}}_{1}}=\\frac{{{\\text{p}}_{1}}+{{\\text{q}}_{2}}}{2}\\Rightarrow {{\\text{x}}_{1}}=\\frac{-\\left\\{ -2\\text{a}+\\text{m}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-{{\\text{m}}^{2}}{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right\\}}{{{\\text{m}}^{2}}}\\Rightarrow \\text{m}=\\frac{2\\text{a}}{{{\\text{y}}_{1}}}$</p><p>Substituting this value of $\\text{m}$ in (i), we obtain</p><p>$\\begin{array}{*{35}{r}} \\text{y}-{{\\text{y}}_{1}} &amp; ~=\\frac{2\\text{a}}{{{\\text{y}}_{1}}}\\left( \\text{x}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right)\\Rightarrow \\text{y}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-\\text{y}_{1}^{2}=2\\text{a}\\left( \\text{x}-{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right) \\\\ \\Rightarrow \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ y}{{\\text{y}}_{1}}-2\\text{a}\\left( \\text{x}+{{\\text{x}}_{1}} \\right) &amp; ~=\\text{y}_{1}^{2}-4\\text{a}{{\\text{x}}_{1}}\\Rightarrow \\text{T}=\\text{{S}'} \\\\ \\end{array}$</p><p>This is the equation of the chord bisected at $\\left( {{\\text{x}}_{1}},{{\\text{y}}_{1}} \\right)$.</p>",
      "position": 1,
      "qcConcept": "66a0dd59c03b9dcaf1afea88"
    }
